2... Nc6 3. Nf3 f5 { A fierce counterattack. } 4. exf5 e4 5. Ne5 Nf6 6. d4
{ It's always useful to grab space in the opening. } 6... d6 7. Bb5 dxe5 8.
fxe5 Bxf5 { Now we should equalize the material and finish development. } 9.
exf6 Qxf6 10. O-O Bd6 11. Nc3 O-O 12. Bc4+ Kh8 13. Nb5
{ With two bishops White will enjoy a small advantage in a calm position. } *

