1. e4 e5 2. f4
{ While working on the course, I found myself in an unusual situation. There is practically no modern theory! So I feel like a pioneer in a way. In this part I'll try to highlight the most frequent directions of the King's Gambit. }
2... d6 3. Nc3
{ 3.Nf3  exf4  would transpose to arguably the best line at Black's disposal, so it is reasonable to dodge that bullet.   On the other hand,  3.d3  is a good way to flee from the field of theoretical battle. }
3... exf4 4. Qf3
{ Almost a novelty. As you can see, White is serious about winning back a pawn! Black has many options here  4...Nc6  ,  4...g5  ,  4...Nf6  ,  4...Qh4+  all of which are covered in thecorresponding chapter. }
*

