3. fxe5 Nxe4 4. Nf3 Be7 5. d3
{ 5.d4  is also possible:  5...d5  6.exd6  cxd6   6...Nxd6  7.Bd3  is also decent.  7.Bd3  d5  8.O-O  Nc6  9.c4  Nb4  10.Be2  looks like a well-known Petroff line without the c7 and f2 pawns. }
