[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. f4 d6
{ One of the calm options. The biggest threat, however, awaits us after the ingenuous  3.Nf3  . }
3. Nc3
{ 3.Nf3  exf4  would transpose toarguably the best line at Black's disposal, so it is reasonable to dodge that bullet.   On the other hand,  3.d3  is a good way to flee from the field of theoretical battle. }
3... Nc6 4. Nf3
{ When the knight is already on c6, we will always have d4-d5 push. } 4... Nd4
{ Does not make too much sense. } 5. d3 c6 { 5...Bg4  can be met by  6.Be2  . }
6. Be2 g6 7. O-O Bg7 8. fxe5 dxe5 9. Nxd4 exd4 10. Nb1
{ This is a typical idea. We are aiming to reroute the knight via Nd2-c4 or f3 depending on the situation. }
10... Nh6 11. Bf4 { With comfortable play ahead for White. } *

