{ When the knight is already on c6, we will always have d4-d5 push. } 4... exf4
5. d4 g5
{ Usually Black is happy to get this setup, but here it seems White has a direct solution: }
6. d5 Ne5 7. Bb5+ Bd7 8. Bxd7+ Nxd7 9. h4 Bg7
{ Other moves are less fortunate. For example, if  9...g4  then  10.Nd4  gives White an advantage.   Another interesting try is  9...Ne7  10.hxg5  Ng6  11.Qd4  Nde5  12.Bxf4!  Nxf4  13.Nxe5  Bg7  14.Qa4+  Kf8  15.Nd7+  Ke7  16.Nf6  h6  17.e5±  and White is almost winning  . }
10. hxg5 Qe7 11. Qe2 O-O-O 12. Bxf4 { Black is doomed to fight for equality. }
