{ A principled move. Another logical try is  5...Nd4  6.Bd3  Nf6  7.Nge2  Ne6  8.Qg3  g6  9.Bc4  Bg7  10.Qh4=  and it's more or less equal. White should first castle followed by d3 and perhaps Bh6 in the future. }
6. Kd1 { Our king always plays an important role! } 6... Nf6 7. Nf3 g6 8. Bc4
Be6
{ 8...Nc6  can be met with  9.d4  Bg7  10.Rf1  with a nice attacking game ahead. }
9. Bxe6 fxe6 10. e5 Nfd5 11. Qg4 Qd7 12. Re1 O-O-O 13. Nxd5 Nxd5 14. d3
{ White is better here. The only question is how to bring the queen's rook into play. }
14... Re8 15. a4 { For example, like this! } 15... Bg7 16. exd6 cxd6 17. Ra3
Rhf8 18. Rb3 Rf5 19. Bd2
{ Rooks are completely in play. Next stop is to transfer our king to safety via Kc1-b1. }
