[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Chapter 3: 2...d6"]
[Black "3.d4!? alternative"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. f4 d6
{ One of the calm options. The biggest threat, however, awaits us after the ingenuous  3.Nf3  . }
3. d4 { Is another interesting alternative. } 3... exd4
{ 3...Nf6  4.Nc3  exd4  5.Qxd4  Nc6  6.Qe3  will transpose into the main line. }
4. Qxd4 Nc6 5. Qe3
{ Looks like the Center Game. With f4 & d6 included it seems to be playable: }
5... Nf6
{ 5...g6  is also possible, but after  6.Nc3  Bg7  7.Bd2  Nf6  8.O-O-O  O-O  9.Nf3  Re8  10.Bc4  threatening ideas like Ng5.  10...Na5  11.Bd3  c6  12.Qe1+=  White has a very comfortable position. }
6. Nc3 Be7 7. Bc4 Be6
{ Black can also try  7...O-O  But White has a comfortable position after  8.Nf3  a6  9.a3  b5  10.Ba2  Be6  11.Bxe6  fxe6  12.O-O  +=  . }
8. Bxe6 fxe6 9. Nf3 d5 10. Qe2 Bb4 11. Bd2 Bxc3 12. Bxc3 Nxe4 13. Bxg7 Rg8 14.
Bc3
{ White seems to be fine here. Note that Black will probably take on c3 after playing ...Qe7 or ...Qd7, so we should castle on the short side. }
