[White "Chapter 4: 2...Nc6"]
[Black "3...exf4 4.d4 d5 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. f4 Nc6
{ Another sideline. A fine developing move, which, however, prevents Black from capturing on f4 and therefore is not dangerous at all. }
3. Nf3 exf4
{ Not the best moment to capture on f4.   3...d6  will probably just transpose to the 2...d6 chapter. }
4. d4 d5 5. exd5 Qxd5 6. Nc3 Bb4 7. Bd3 Qe6+
{ This is more or less the same, we need to move our king to f2, but Black spent time on ...Qe6+ too. }
8. Kf2
{ Followed by Re1-Bf4, Black should also be careful of Nb5 ideas. We retain a slightly better position. }
*

