1. e4 e5 2. f4 Nc6
{ Another sideline. A fine developing move, which, however, prevents Black from capturing on f4 and therefore is not dangerous at all. }
3. Nf3 d5 { is not as bad as it might seem } 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. Nc3 Qe6 6. Be2 Bc5
{ Black tries to hinder our development. This could work if it weren't for Nxe5! }
7. Nxe5 Nxe5 8. d4 { A good old trick! } 8... Nf3+
{ Black needs to complicate the matters. } 9. gxf3 Be7 10. O-O Bd7
{ Black tries to castle queenside and get to our king on g1. } 11. d5 Qb6+ 12.
Kh1 O-O-O 13. Ne4 Nh6 14. a4 a5 15. b4
{ One of the tempting ways to develop initiative. } 15... Bxb4 16. Rb1
{ Our king is more or less safe at the moment. Meanwhile, White developed a nice initiative on the queenside. c2-c3 is the first of many threats black needs to deal with. }
