{ Another sideline. A fine developing move, which, however, prevents Black from capturing on f4 and therefore is not dangerous at all. }
3. Nf3 f5 { Nakamura played this against Ivanchuk. } 4. exf5
{ I'd suggest to choose this move, which enforces Black to play precisely.   4.d3  is also very nice and simple direction which probably gives White better chances.  d6  5.Nc3  Nf6  6.g3  g6  7.Bg2  Bg7  8.fxe5  dxe5∞  as in 1-0 Ivanchuk, V. - Nakamura, H. Cap d'Agde 2010. }
4... e4 5. Ne5 Nf6 6. d4 d6
{ A calm alternative. Black accepts a slightly worse position. } 7. Bb5 dxe5 8.
fxe5 Bxf5 9. exf6 Qxf6 10. O-O O-O-O 11. Bxc6 bxc6 12. g4
{ Black has no compensation for the piece whatsoever. } *

