[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Chapter 5. 2...d5 - the Falkbeer Countergambit"]
[Black "3...c6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. f4 d5
{ The Falkbeer Countergambit is a fair and time-tested way to handle the King's Gambit. }
3. exd5 c6 { This is the so-called Nimzowitsch Variation. } 4. Ne2
{ An interesting way to develop the kingside while preparing the f4-e5 capture.   4.Qe2  cxd5  5.fxe5  Nc6  6.Nf3  Bg4  7.Nc3  Nge7  8.d4  Nxd4  9.Qf2  Nxf3  10.gxf3  Be6  11.Bg5  is another idea. }
4... exf4 5. Nxf4 cxd5 6. d4 { Now we can focus on the isolated pawn. } 6...
Nf6 7. Bb5+ Nc6 8. O-O Bg4 9. Be2 Bxe2 10. Nxe2
{ White has obvious targets to attack and a few simple moves to develop an initiative. }
*

