{ 5.d4  is also possible.   5...Nf6  6.Bxf4  Qe4+  7.Qe2  Qxe2+  8.Bxe2  Nd5  9.Bd2+=  1-0 Zvjaginsev, V. - Wang, H. Taiyuan 2007.  5...Bd6  6.c4  Qe6+  7.Be2  c6  8.Nc3  Nf6  9.O-O  O-O  10.Bd3  is a bit unclear. But White has nothing to worry about. The idea is to develop via Qc2-Bd2-Rae1. }
