{ White has a wide choice here:  5.c4  ,  5.Bc4  ,  5.Be2  ,  5.d4  and  5.Nc3  . I'd suggest to try }
5. Bb5+
{ Many famous players have tested this variation in the past. In particular, Nakamura, Zvjaginsev and Savchenko tried this move. }
5... Bd7
{ This is another continuation. White will have good chances to play for an advantage in this case. }
6. Bxd7+ Qxd7 7. O-O Nxd5 8. c4 Nb6 9. d4 Nxc4 10. Qe2+
{ Is another try, but not as effective. } 10... Qe6 11. Qd3 Ne3
{ Black needs to be precise.  11...Be7  12.Bxf4  Nb6  13.Bxc7  gives White a good position. }
12. Ng5 { Everything is now forced for both sides. } 12... Qg6 13. Qb5+ c6 14.
Qxb7 Qxg5 15. Bxe3 fxe3 16. Qxa8 Bd6 17. Nc3 Qh4 18. g3 Bxg3 19. hxg3 Qxg3+ 20.
Kh1 { Leads to a perpetual. } *

