6. Bxd5 Nf6 7. Nxh4 { In their game, Short went  7.Bb3  . } 7... Nxd5 8. exd5
Qxh4 9. Qe2+ Kd8 10. Qf2 Qxf2+ 11. Kxf2
{ Leads to a very pleasant endgame for White. The aim is to develop pieces on the queenside via c4-Nc3-d3 and target the f4-pawn, if Black tries for g5 we have h4 ideas. }
