1. e4 e5 2. f4 exf4 3. Nf3 Ne7
{ A favorite move of Etienne Bacrot. Black wants to protect the f4-pawn with the knight from g6 or d5. }
4. d4 d5 5. Bd3 dxe4 6. Bxe4 Ng6 7. Qe2 Be7 8. h4
{ Trying to use the awkward placement of the black knight. } 8... Nxh4
{ Looks almost like a suicide. } 9. Nc3
{ Simple developing move, our idea is to take on f4 next. } 9... Nxf3+ 10. Qxf3
g5
{ Looks extremely risky as Black's King wont be able to castle anytime soon. We will just continue developing. }
11. Bd2 Nd7 12. O-O-O Nf6 13. Rde1 Kf8 14. g3
{ Is just great for White. Black's king remains in a dangerous position. } *

