[Black "3...h6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. f4 exf4 3. Nf3 h6
{ A rare move, which was played by many strong grandmasters: Leko, Almasi, McShane, Ganguly, Alekseev and so on. The main idea is to prevent  3...g5  4.h4  line. But now White is in time to grab the center. }
4. d4 g5 5. g3
{ Using the fact that Black can't reply with the usual ...g5-g4 in this case. }
5... fxg3 { 5...g4?  allows  6.Ne5±  . } 6. hxg3 Bg7 7. Nc3 d6 8. Be3 Bg4 9.
Be2 Nc6 10. Qd2 Nge7 11. O-O-O Qd7
{ Black prepares to castle long. We can use the unguarded b5-square to our advantage. }
12. d5 Ne5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. Bd4 Ng6
{ Best move. If Black plays  14...O-O-O  then  15.Bxe5  dxe5  16.Rhf1  is strong with pressure on the f-file. After something like  16...Bxe2  17.Qxe2  Rhf8  18.Rf6  the f- and h-pawns are both weak, White is clearly pushing. }
15. Bb5 c6 16. Be2 { Now the black king doesn't have a safe harbour. } *

