14. Bxg5 f6 15. Rxh8+ Bxh8 16. Bf4
{ And we reach a complicated position where once again White is willing to give up a piece for dynamic compensation. White should try to aim for a4-a5 and also Rh1 ideas. One sample line is: }
16... Qe7 17. a4 Bg7 18. a5 Nd7 19. Qe2 Nf8 20. a6
{ With very nice compensation. Some forced lines, as usual, lead to a draw: }
20... b6 21. Ba4 b5 22. Nxb5 cxb5 23. Qxb5+ Bd7 24. Qh5+ Kd8
{ 24...Qf7  is not as delightful as after  25.Bxd7+  Nxd7  26.Qxg4  White enjoys a small edge. }
25. Qa5+ { Leading to a perpetual. } *

