[Black "4.Bc4 g5 --- 12.d3"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. f4 exf4
{ 'The refutation of any gambit begins with accepting it. In my opinion the King's Gambit is busted. It loses by force.' - R. Fischer, A Bust to the King's Gambit. }
3. Nf3 d6
{ The best move according to Stockfish and Robert James Fischer. Calling this move the refutation is still an exaggeration, but I'd say this is the line with the least fun for White. }
4. Bc4 { White anticipates the ...g5-move. } 4... g5
{ Leads to drawish positions with minor chances for White. } 5. h4 h6 6. hxg5
Bg7 7. gxh6 Rxh6 8. Rxh6 Bxh6
{ Surprisingly, despite the material is equal and White's stronger center, Black is right in time with his response. }
9. Nc3 Nc6 10. Qe2 Bg4 11. Qf2 Bg7
{ Black is in time to prevent d4 and create counterplay. } 12. d3 Bxf3 13. gxf3
{ 13.Qxf3  Bxc3+!  14.bxc3  Ne5  15.Qxf4  Nxc4  16.dxc4  leads to a highly compromised pawn structure, although the position is still equal because of White's extra pawn. }
13... Bd4 14. Qh2
{ This is more logical, to cover the h4-square.   14.Qg2!?  White can even win an exchange, but, alas, this is only enough for a draw.  14...Qh4+  15.Ke2  Nf6   15...Nge7  16.Bd2  Kd7  17.Rh1  Rg8  18.Qf1  Qf6  is equal too.  16.Be3!  is a beautiful idea to trap the black queen, but sadly, it's not enough:  16...fxe3  17.Rh1  Qf2+   17...Qf4  18.Rh8+  Ke7  19.Rxa8  Ne5  20.Nd5+  Nxd5  21.Bxd5  c6  22.Bb3  Ng6  23.c3  Qh4  24.Kd1  Nf4  25.Qg8  Qh1+  26.Kc2  Qh2+  27.Kb1  Qh1+=  18.Qxf2  exf2  19.Rh8+  Kd7  20.Rxa8  Nh5!  White can't avoid a very deep repetition after  21.Rg8  Ne5  22.Nd1  Nf4+  23.Kf1  Nxf3  24.Nxf2  Nh2+  25.Ke1  Nf3+=  A lovely book draw. }
14... Ne5 15. Qxf4 Bxc3+ 16. bxc3 Nxc4 17. dxc4
{ Our pawns on the c-file are too weak to play for an advantage. } 17... Ne7
18. c5 Ng6 19. Qg5
{ White can't avoid the trade of queens to due the constant threat of ...Qh4+. }
19... dxc5 20. Qxd8+ Rxd8 21. Be3 Ne5 22. Ke2 Nc4 23. Rh1
{ The pawn structure is similar to the Berlin endgame. Black basically did everything right. }
*

