19. Re1+ Kd8 20. Ne5 b5 21. b3 Re8 22. Bf4 f6 23. Nd3
{ Now an opposite-color bishop endgame will appear. Not so much fun, indeed, but draw is surely OK when we play King's Gambit for White! }
23... Bf8 24. Rhe3 Rxe3 25. Rxe3 g5 26. Bg3 Kd7 27. Nc5+ Bxc5 28. dxc5
{ For perfectionists, I can add one of the logical forcing lines:  28...Rg8  29.Rd3  Kc6  30.Bxc7  gxh4  31.Rd2  Bxg2+   31...Kxc5  32.Bf4=  32.Rxg2  Rxg2  33.Kxg2  Kxc7  34.b4  f5  35.Kh3  f4  36.Kxh4  h5  37.Kh3= }
