{ 6.Nxg4  is just bad because of  6...d5  . } 6... Qf6 7. Nc3 Nxe5 8. dxe5 Qxe5
9. Qxg4 Bh6 { 9...d6  10.Qf3  Bh6  transposes to the mainline. } 10. Qf3 d6 11.
Be2 Be6 12. Nb5
{ 12.Rf1  is also possible, but boring:  12...O-O-O  13.Bxf4  Qxf4  14.Qxf4  Bxf4  15.Rxf4  Ne7  16.Rf6  Rdg8  17.Kf2  Rg6  18.Rxg6  fxg6  19.Ke3=  . }
12... O-O-O 13. Bd2 d5 14. exd5 Bxd5 15. Qh3+ Be6 16. Bc3
{ Looks exciting, but will likely end in a draw as usual. } 16... Qc5 17. Qf3
f6 18. b4 Qe7 19. O-O Bd5 20. Qh3+ Kb8 21. Rae1
{ With decent counterplay. Black should exchange the queens right away, which should equalise matters. }
*

