7... g5 { 7...d6  8.Bxf4  gives White a large advantage in development. } 8. h4
g4 { It is also possible to play more restraint. } 9. Ng1
{ Black is more or less forced to play f3. } 9... f3 { Now a sample line is }
10. gxf3 d6 11. e6 { 11.exd6  Bxd6  12.Qe2+  Be6  13.Bg5  is possible too. }
11... Bxe6 12. fxg4 h6
{ Trying to prevent g4-g5, is well met by White's next move. } 13. Nh3 Qxh4+
14. Nf2 Qe7 15. Be3
{ White has excellent play for the pawn. The queen will go to d2/f3 and, as usual, we will castle queenside. }
