12. Qe4 b4 13. Nb5 { The most interesting option we have at our disposal. }
13... f5
{ The knight is untouchable, as  13...cxb5  14.d6!  Bh4+  15.g3!  costs Black material. }
14. Qd4 cxb5 15. Bxb5+ Kf7 16. d6 Bh4+ 17. Kf1
{ The alternative  17.Nxh4  Qxh4+  18.Qf2  Qxf2+  19.Kxf2  is an interesting endgame, but it objectively shouldn't promise White much. For instance  19...Rc8  20.Re1  Ke6  21.Ba4  Na6  preparing Nc5, basically forcing the repetition, as neither side can sidestep from the moves  22.Bb3+  Kd7  23.Ba4+  with a draw. }
17... Bxf3 18. gxf3 g6 19. Bxf4 Nxf4 20. Qxf4
{ A rather long and forced line leads to this position, which is equal according to engines, but, one can't deny it, it looks really tasty! }
