{ This looks bad because of White's next move, but Black has enough resources. }
13. d5 a6 14. dxc6 { 14.Ba4  b5!  unpins the knight and simply wins. } 14...
axb5 15. cxb7 Rb8 16. Bd2
{ Intending to castle queenside in order to create pressure along the d-file. }
16... Bxc3 17. Bxc3 O-O 18. h4
{ It's very important to prevent Black from stabilizing the position, otherwise, the extra pawn may start counting. }
18... Qd7 19. hxg5 Rfd8 20. Qxf4 Qd3 21. Rf1 Qg6 22. Qg4
{ There are usually no winners in such a shootout. This will likely end in a draw as well. }
